{"lemma":"جارِحَةٍ","slug":"جارِحَةٍ","root":"ج.ر.ح","root_slug":"ج-ر-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ر-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5463"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5463","headword_ar":"جَارِحَةٌ","root":"jrH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawaAriHu","text_ar":"جَوَارِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, L, Msb, TA.) ―         -b2-  The latter signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beasts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"birds, of prey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that catch game;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * Mgh, L, Msb, K:) thus the falcon is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jArHp","text_ar":"جارحة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so is the dog trained for hunting, because it gains for its owner: (L:) and this appellation is applied alike to the male and the female, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAHilapN","text_ar":"رَاحِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAwiyapN","text_ar":"رَاوِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"members,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limbs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which things are gained"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earned;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one works;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) as the hands or arms, and the feet or legs: (S, A, K, TA:) because they gain, or earn, or do, good and evil. (TA.) ―         -b4-  [And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"organs"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the body: thus, for instance,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jArHp","text_ar":"جارحة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied (in the Msb, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bSr","text_ar":"بصر"},{"kind":"text","text":",) to the eye, which is termed (in the TA in that art.) the seeing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jArHp","text_ar":"جارحة"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaAriHapu Aln~aAZirapu","text_ar":"الجَارِحَةُ النَّاظِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":").] ―         -b5-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mares:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] because they bring gain to their owners by their breeding. (AA, T.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lahu jaAriHapN","text_ar":"مَا لَهُ جَارِحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He possesses not a female beast that bears young: he possesses not that which makes gain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi Aln~aAqapu mino jawaAriHi AlmaAli","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ النَّاقَةُ مِنْ جَوَارِحِ المَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h*h AlA^ataAnu","text_ar":"هذه الاَتَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h*h Alfarasu","text_ar":"هذه الفَرَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This she-camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this she-ass,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this mare, is young, unimpaired by age"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqobilapN","text_ar":"مُقْبِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqotabalapN","text_ar":"مُقْتَبَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the womb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in youthful vigour, and one of which the offspring is wished for."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["L","S","A","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}